The early years of a slow motion slide into fascism doesn‚Äôt look like goose-stepping soldiers in Hugo Boss uniforms. It looks like reasonable people with important platforms saying ‚Äúhey, everyone should have a voice, let‚Äôs explore their ideas in open debate‚Äù

He was not his own definition of an Uber-mensch. His friends weren‚Äôt either. They were the dregs. And it took years for them to gain any actual power. But they did it by normalizing the horrible things they were saying

They were, for the most part, not the most popular kids on the block. Kind of hard to make friends when your ideas are all repugnant! Hitler himself was a failed art student, minor soldier who puffed up his own credentials, who was apparently homeless for a while

People are always talking about the alt-right, neo-Nazis, KKK, etc like ‚Äúugh, these losers, no one takes them seriously, don‚Äôt call them Nazis when they‚Äôre nothing like REAL Nazis‚Äù and like...who do you people think the ‚Äúreal‚Äù Nazis were?

Hitler didn‚Äôt start with ‚Äúkill all the ‚Äòundesirables‚Äô.‚Äù He started with ‚Äúseparate them from ‚Äònormal‚Äô people‚Äù then ‚Äúdeport them‚Äù then ‚Äúdeport them to labor camps‚Äù and THEN ‚Äústraight up murder.‚Äù Each step, once it had gradually been accepted by the population, greasing the ramp.
